<script lang="ts">
  const html: string = "<h1>Breadcrumb Link</h1>\n\n<p>A breadcrumb link is a navigational anchor element representing one step in a breadcrumb trail. It renders as a semantic <code>&lt;a&gt;</code> element and is designed to be placed inside a BreadcrumbListItem within a BreadcrumbList and BreadcrumbNav structure.</p>\n\n<h2>Implementation Notes</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Renders as a semantic <code>&lt;a&gt;</code> element for breadcrumb navigation</li>\n<li>Designed to be used inside a BreadcrumbListItem</li>\n<li>Supports an optional <code>aria-label</code> override for more descriptive screen reader text</li>\n<li>All link text is provided through the children slot</li>\n<li>Spreads <code>...restProps</code> onto the <code>&lt;a&gt;</code> element</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Props</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li><code>href</code>: string (required) -- the URL to navigate to</li>\n<li><code>label</code>: string (optional, default: undefined) -- accessible label override via <code>aria-label</code></li>\n<li><code>children</code>: slot (required) -- the link text/content</li>\n<li><code>...restProps</code>: Any additional HTML attributes spread onto the <code>&lt;a&gt;</code></li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Usage</h2>\n\n<pre><code class=\"language-html\">&lt;BreadcrumbNav label=\"Breadcrumb\"&gt;\n  &lt;BreadcrumbList&gt;\n    &lt;BreadcrumbListItem&gt;\n      &lt;BreadcrumbLink href=\"/\"&gt;Home&lt;/BreadcrumbLink&gt;\n    &lt;/BreadcrumbListItem&gt;\n    &lt;BreadcrumbListItem&gt;\n      &lt;BreadcrumbLink href=\"/health-a-z\"&gt;Health A to Z&lt;/BreadcrumbLink&gt;\n    &lt;/BreadcrumbListItem&gt;\n    &lt;BreadcrumbListItem aria-current=\"page\"&gt;\n      Diabetes\n    &lt;/BreadcrumbListItem&gt;\n  &lt;/BreadcrumbList&gt;\n&lt;/BreadcrumbNav&gt;</code></pre>\n\n<h2>Keyboard Interactions</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Tab: Focus the link</li>\n<li>Enter: Activate the link (browser default)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>ARIA</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Implicit <code>link</code> role from the <code>&lt;a&gt;</code> element</li>\n<li><code>aria-label</code> -- optional override for descriptive screen reader text, set from the <code>label</code> prop</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>When to Use</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Use inside BreadcrumbListItem to create a clickable link to an ancestor page</li>\n<li>Use to provide navigation to parent or grandparent pages in the site hierarchy</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>When Not to Use</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Do not use for the current page -- the current page should not be a link in the breadcrumb trail</li>\n<li>Do not use outside of BreadcrumbListItem -- use ActionLink or a standard anchor for standalone links</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Headless</h2>\n\n<p>This component provides a semantic <code>&lt;a&gt;</code> element with optional <code>aria-label</code> override and zero visual styling. The consumer is responsible for all CSS including link color, underline style, hover effects, and focus indicators.</p>\n\n<h2>Styles</h2>\n\n<p>The consumer provides all CSS styling. The component renders with a <code>.breadcrumb-link</code> class for targeting. No default styles are included — this is a fully headless component.</p>\n\n<h2>Testing</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Verify the component renders an <code>&lt;a&gt;</code> element with class <code>breadcrumb-link</code></li>\n<li>Verify <code>aria-label</code> is set from the <code>label</code> prop</li>\n<li>Verify keyboard interactions work correctly</li>\n<li>Verify pass-through attributes are applied</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Advice</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Designers</strong>: Style breadcrumb links to be visually distinct from the current page text. Use consistent color and underline treatments across all breadcrumb links.</li>\n<li><strong>Developers</strong>: Use the <code>label</code> prop to provide descriptive screen reader text when the visible text is abbreviated.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Composition</h2>\n\n<p>BreadcrumbLink follows the Nav / List / ListItem composition pattern:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>BreadcrumbNav</strong> -- outer <code>&lt;nav&gt;</code> container providing the navigation landmark.</li>\n<li><strong>BreadcrumbList</strong> -- <code>&lt;ol&gt;</code> list conveying the ordered hierarchy.</li>\n<li><strong>BreadcrumbListItem</strong> -- individual <code>&lt;li&gt;</code> items.</li>\n<li><strong>BreadcrumbLink</strong> -- <code>&lt;a&gt;</code> link inside a list item for navigable ancestor pages.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<pre><code class=\"language-html\">&lt;BreadcrumbNav label=\"Breadcrumb\"&gt;\n  &lt;BreadcrumbList&gt;\n    &lt;BreadcrumbListItem&gt;\n      &lt;BreadcrumbLink href=\"/\"&gt;Home&lt;/BreadcrumbLink&gt;\n    &lt;/BreadcrumbListItem&gt;\n    &lt;BreadcrumbListItem&gt;\n      &lt;BreadcrumbLink href=\"/health-a-z\"&gt;Health A to Z&lt;/BreadcrumbLink&gt;\n    &lt;/BreadcrumbListItem&gt;\n    &lt;BreadcrumbListItem aria-current=\"page\"&gt;\n      Diabetes\n    &lt;/BreadcrumbListItem&gt;\n  &lt;/BreadcrumbList&gt;\n&lt;/BreadcrumbNav&gt;</code></pre>\n\n<h2>Related components</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li><code>breadcrumb-nav</code> — a navigation container for breadcrumb trail links</li>\n<li><code>breadcrumb-list</code> — an ordered list of breadcrumb list items</li>\n<li><code>breadcrumb-list-item</code> — one breadcrumb list item in the trail</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>References</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>WAI-ARIA Breadcrumb Pattern: https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/breadcrumb/</li>\n</ul>";
</script>

